    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1653" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐδή</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῆς</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">voice</span>, properly the human voice with
          reference to its pleasing effects; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τοῦ καὶ ἀπὸ
            γλώσσης μέλιτος γλυκίων ῥέεν αὐδή</span>, of Nestor as orator,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 1.249</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; θεοῖς ἐναλίγκιος αὐδήν</span>, Phemius, the
          minstrel, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.371</span></i>; said of a bird,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἣ δ̓</span> (the bowstring) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπὸ κᾱλὸν ἄεισε, χελῑδόνι εἰκέλη αὐδήν</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 21.411</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
